                  <listApp>
                  	
                  	<app loc="3">
                  		<lem>kiṭa<choice><orig>ṉ</orig><reg>n</reg></choice><supplied reason="lost">ta <hi rend="grantha">bhūmi</hi>yai</supplied></lem>
                  		<note>Restoration base on parallel in in #2<!--update ref--> line 4.</note>
                  	</app>
                     <app loc="6">
                        <lem>m<choice><orig>i</orig><reg>ī</reg></choice><choice><unclear>ṉa</unclear><unclear>ṉ</unclear></choice> p<choice><unclear>o</unclear><unclear>ō</unclear></choice>ṉṉum</lem>
                        <note>Dr. G. Vijayavenugopal (personal communication) suggested to interpret <foreign>poṉṉum</foreign> as "gold", to consider previous word <foreign>mīṉa</foreign> as a mistake for <foreign>īḻa</foreign> (<foreign>īḻam</foreign>), and to understand "Lankan gold". The mention of gold, however, would not make much sense in the contewt. There are a few other possibilities, although none is entirely sactifactory: (1) <foreign>pōṉṉum</foreign>, thus land, "where the fishes (<foreign>mīṉ</foreign>) go (<foreign>pōṉṉum</foreign>)" or "where the elevation (<foreign>mīṉ</foreign>) goes (<foreign>pōṉṉum</foreign>)"; (2) <foreign>poṉṉum</foreign>, mistake for <foreign>poḷḷum</foreign>, thus, land "where the elevated (<foreign>mī</foreign>) path (<foreign>ṉa</foreign>, for <foreign>naṭai</foreign>) was dug (<foreign>poḷḷum</foreign>). This second possibility is based on a similar formula found in #7 <!--update ref-->: <foreign>Ikkuḷattiṉ minaṭai poḷḷak kuḷattilē kalluvat' ākavum</foreign>. <!--I have translated it as: we have to clear (<foreign>kalluvatākavum</foreign>) in the tank (<foreign>kuḷattilē</foreign>), in order to dig (<foreign>poḷḷa</foreign>) [for] an elevated (<foreign>mī</foreign>) road/path (<foreign>naṭai</foreign>) of this tank (<foreign>ikkuḷattiṉ</foreign>).--> <!--Unnecessary: there will be a link to this inscription.--></note>
                     </app>
                     <app loc="6">
                        <lem><unclear>Aka</unclear>vēriyum puṟavēriyum</lem>
                        <note>Literally: "the inner lake (<foreign>aka-v-ēri-y-um</foreign>) and the outer lake (<foreign>puṟa-v-ēri-y-um</foreign>)". This probably refers to a type of land, but the details remain unclear. See also #7 <!--update ref--> for a similar formula.</note>
                     </app>
                  </listApp>
